page.title: 15Birdwatch In Cleobury
page.content: In my garden are many birds. In the trees are nuthatches and treecreepers. In a big beech tree are tawny owls and little owls. Blue tits and great tits nest in our birdboxes. Long-tailed tits and coal tits also visit. We see goldfinches, chaffinches and bullfinches and have some nesting greenfinches. Nesting are thrushes and blackbirds and, in our grape vine, a spotted flycatcher. I think that some goldcrests are nesting somewhere near by. Starlings nest in our roof and sparrows, dunnocks and robins eat our rabbit food. Mallards and crows fly overhead, also swifts, swallows and house martins. Magpies pester the crows and rooks. In winter male and female blackcaps come. Last winter five fieldfares and thirty redwings came. In the trees near our pond is a great spotted woodpecker.
